  "prompt": "Should you rinse with water after mouthwash?",
  "response": "It is generally not recommended to rinse your mouth with water immediately after using mouthwash. Doing so can wash away the active ingredients in the mouthwash that are intended to provide benefits such as antibacterial action, freshening breath, or strengthening teeth. \n\nFor optimal effectiveness, it's typically advised to avoid eating or drinking for at least 30 minutes after using mouthwash, allowing the ingredients to remain in contact with your teeth and gums. However, if the mouthwash is specifically designed for rinsing (such as those that are not therapeutic), checking the instructions on the label may provide the best guidance. Always refer to the recommendations provided with your specific mouthwash product.",
